Chen Xuan is an award-winning architect, designer and entrepreneur based in Beijing. Her first experience with architectural design was in 1999. In 2004, she established her design studio, Shishang Architecture, and has since made a name for herself in her field. Some of her projects include the 2008 Beijing Olympic Park Public Service Building, the UCCA Shop, LOFT in Beijing, and Sui Jianguo Museum. Here's her story of how she continues to break boundaries in the exploration and possibilities of space.